<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=64caa1b6-f037-4a08-8cfd-0242fb70fd77">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="Task-4-%E2%80%94-AQI-Distribution-Analysis">Task 4 — AQI Distribution Analysis<a class="anchor-link" href="#Task-4-%E2%80%94-AQI-Distribution-Analysis">¶</a></h2><p>The board asked two things:</p>
<ol>
<li>Where do most cities cluster on the AQI scale?</li>
<li>Is the average AQI being pulled up by a few extreme cities?</li>
</ol>
<p>For question 1 — I will use a histogram.
A histogram shows where most values sit and the shape of the spread.</p>
<p>For question 2 — I will use a boxplot.
A boxplot shows the middle value, the spread, and any extreme points
as individual dots outside the whiskers.</p>
<p>I need two plots because one plot cannot answer both questions clearly.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs" id="cell-id=e7707a5c-628c-45bd-ace8-69e92b7157e7">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [67]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>

<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'city_day.csv'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># remove rows where AQI is missing</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dropna</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">subset</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="c1"># remove values that are not possible in real life</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">&gt;=</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">&lt;=</span> <span class="mi">1000</span><span class="p">]</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=75b16d28-e892-4d64-9115-b18176a8b076">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [134]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">mean_aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">city_df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">mean</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">median_aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">city_df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">median</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Mean AQI :"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nb">round</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">mean_aqi</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Median AQI :"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nb">round</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">median_aqi</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">))</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell-outputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-OutputCollapser jp-Cell-outputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-OutputArea jp-Cell-outputArea">
<div class="jp-OutputArea-child">
<div class="jp-OutputPrompt jp-OutputArea-prompt"></div>
<div class="jp-RenderedText jp-OutputArea-output" data-mime-type="text/plain" tabindex="0">
<pre>Mean AQI : 166.46
Median AQI : 118.0
</pre>
</div>
