<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=b80b8d07-28fe-40de-b667-d5dc43372725">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="Two-Observations-for-the-Pollution-Control-Board">Two Observations for the Pollution Control Board<a class="anchor-link" href="#Two-Observations-for-the-Pollution-Control-Board">¶</a></h2><p>Observation 1:
Most AQI values are concentrated in the low to moderate AQI range according to the histogram.</p>
<p>Observation 2:
The box plot shows several extreme AQI values. Since the mean AQI is higher than the median AQI, a few highly polluted cities are increasing the average AQI.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=939739b3-a881-4681-9887-3132de16c231">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="Task-5-%E2%80%94-Finding-and-Fixing-Extreme-AQI-Values">Task 5 — Finding and Fixing Extreme AQI Values<a class="anchor-link" href="#Task-5-%E2%80%94-Finding-and-Fixing-Extreme-AQI-Values">¶</a></h2><p>The team lead said "handle extreme values properly" but did not say how.
So I need to first find them, then decide what to do.</p>
<p><strong>How I will find them — IQR method</strong>
IQR means Interquartile Range.
It is the gap between the 25th and 75th percentile of the data.
Any value above Q3 + 1.5 x IQR is considered an extreme value.</p>
<p>I chose IQR over using the mean because the mean itself gets
pulled up by extreme values — so it is not a reliable reference point.
IQR only looks at the middle 50% of the data which is more stable.</p>
<p><strong>Should I delete extreme values?</strong>
Not always. Three options exist:</p>
<ul>
<li>Delete — only if the value is physically impossible
like AQI of 9999 or a negative number</li>
<li>Cap — replace the extreme value with the boundary value
use this when the reading might be real but exaggerated</li>
<li>Keep — if the dataset is small and the value seems genuine</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>My decision:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Any AQI below 0 will be deleted — physically impossible</li>
<li>Any AQI above the IQR upper boundary will be capped
because very high pollution can genuinely happen in India
but extreme spikes distort the statistics unfairly</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs" id="cell-id=f6ec3957-b8e3-4c9b-8c9a-f7de3ba24781">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [136]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>

<span class="n">city_df</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"city_day.csv"</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=3e4b0ea3-7776-4290-996e-422f93e8a7ab">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [137]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">q1</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">city_df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">quantile</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mf">0.25</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">q3</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">city_df</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">quantile</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mf">0.75</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">iqr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">q3</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">q1</span>

<span class="n">upper_limit</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">q3</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="mf">1.5</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">iqr</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Q1 :"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">q1</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Q3 :"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">q3</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"IQR :"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">iqr</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Upper Limit :"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">upper_limit</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell-outputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-OutputCollapser jp-Cell-outputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-OutputArea jp-Cell-outputArea">
<div class="jp-OutputArea-child">
<div class="jp-OutputPrompt jp-OutputArea-prompt"></div>
<div class="jp-RenderedText jp-OutputArea-output" data-mime-type="text/plain" tabindex="0">
<pre>Q1 : 81.0
Q3 : 208.0
IQR : 127.0
Upper Limit : 398.5
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=6f5ae74b-c9f4-47c1-b83f-5d199b672608">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [73]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># count how many values are affected</span>

<span class="n">below_zero</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">above_upper</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="n">upper</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Values below 0 (impossible) :"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">below_zero</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Values above upper fence    :"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">above_upper</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Total affected              :"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">below_zero</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">above_upper</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell-outputWrapper">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-OutputCollapser jp-Cell-outputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-OutputArea jp-Cell-outputArea">
<div class="jp-OutputArea-child">
<div class="jp-OutputPrompt jp-OutputArea-prompt"></div>
<div class="jp-RenderedText jp-OutputArea-output" data-mime-type="text/plain" tabindex="0">
<pre>Values below 0 (impossible) : 0
Values above upper fence    : 1358
Total affected              : 1358
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs" id="cell-id=eb7736e8-6d0c-4dd8-80b6-d562f4ebeaee">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [74]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># save original AQI before making changes</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI_original"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">copy</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="c1"># delete rows where AQI is below 0</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">&gt;=</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="c1"># cap values above the upper fence</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">clip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">upper</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">upper</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=ed5ba8c9-7356-486b-a301-daa0fbe7b772">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
