<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=1f0c3c2a-1dbf-4f49-b791-a9da96e0a59f">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="Two-Most-Interesting-Relationships">Two Most Interesting Relationships<a class="anchor-link" href="#Two-Most-Interesting-Relationships">¶</a></h2><p><strong>Relationship 1 — Area and Production are strongly correlated</strong>
States that farm more land produce more crop overall. This is
expected and confirms the data is internally consistent. It also
tells us that farm size is the biggest driver of output — not
air quality.</p>
<p><strong>Relationship 2 — AQI and Production show a weak or near zero link</strong>
There is no strong direct relationship between a state's average
AQI and its total crop production at this level. This does not mean
air quality has no effect on farming. It means the effect is hidden
by other much stronger factors like farm size, rainfall, irrigation
and soil type — none of which are in this dataset. The relationship
may also be too slow and gradual to show up in a single year of
matched data.</p>
<p><strong>Important limitation:</strong>
The crop data only goes up to 2015 so the merge only covers that
one year. A proper analysis would need crop data from 2015 to 2023
to match the full AQI time range.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=86dad157-13b6-4cf8-acdb-cac076edffe5">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="Task-9-%E2%80%94-Briefing-for-the-State-Environment-Minister">Task 9 — Briefing for the State Environment Minister<a class="anchor-link" href="#Task-9-%E2%80%94-Briefing-for-the-State-Environment-Minister">¶</a></h2><p><strong>To:</strong> The Honourable State Environment Minister
<strong>From:</strong> Data Analysis Team
<strong>Subject:</strong> Air Quality and Farming — What the Data Shows</p>
<hr/>
<p><strong>Finding 1 — Most Indian cities breathe polluted air year round</strong>
The majority of cities in our dataset consistently record air quality
levels in the Moderate to Poor range. This is not a problem limited
to one or two industrial cities — it is widespread across the country.</p>
<p><strong>Finding 2 — Pollution spikes every October to December without fail</strong>
Every single year in the data, air quality gets measurably worse in
the October to December period. This lines up exactly with the time
when farmers burn leftover crop material after the harvest. January
and February also stay polluted because cold winter air traps
everything close to the ground.</p>
<p><strong>Finding 3 — Air quality has shown mild improvement in recent years</strong>
The yearly trend shows that average pollution levels in the most
recent years are slightly lower than in 2015 and 2016. However the
improvement is small and uneven — it is not yet a clear consistent
drop that we can confidently attribute to any specific policy.</p>
<p><strong>Recommended Action</strong>
Launch targeted stubble management support programmes — such as
subsidies for machines that recycle crop waste instead of burning it
— specifically in the October to December window and in the states
where both farming activity and pollution are highest.</p>
<p><strong>Honest Limitation</strong>
This data shows that burning season and pollution spikes happen at
the same time. It does not prove that burning is the only cause.
Cold weather, vehicle emissions and industrial activity all peak
in the same winter months. A field-level study tracking actual
burning locations would be needed before making burning bans the
single policy response.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=b822764a-67e3-4f53-bab1-c7b8e88ed9c4">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="Task-A-%E2%80%94-Do-the-Most-and-Least-Polluted-States-Tell-the-Same-Story?">Task A — Do the Most and Least Polluted States Tell the Same Story?<a class="anchor-link" href="#Task-A-%E2%80%94-Do-the-Most-and-Least-Polluted-States-Tell-the-Same-Story?">¶</a></h2><p>Hidden question here is: does high pollution mean low crop output?
If the hypothesis is true, the most polluted states should show
lower production than the cleanest states.</p>
<p>But the data might surprise us — a state can be polluted AND
productive at the same time if the pollution comes from the
farming itself (like burning stubble after harvest).</p>
<p>I will find the top 5 most polluted and top 5 least polluted
states from the AQI data, then compare their crop production
using a bar chart side by side.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=d4ee8433-d28b-4dd6-9aa1-8c0d0aac1a7a">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [100]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>

<span class="c1"># load files</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"city_day.csv"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">crop</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"crop_production.csv"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># prepare AQI</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Date"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Date"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">errors</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"coerce"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Year"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Date"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">year</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dropna</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">subset</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Year"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">&gt;=</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">&lt;=</span> <span class="mi">1000</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="c1"># map city to state</span>
<span class="n">city_to_state</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="s2">"Ahmedabad"</span>          <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Gujarat"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Delhi"</span>              <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Delhi"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Mumbai"</span>             <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Maharashtra"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Chennai"</span>            <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Tamil Nadu"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Kolkata"</span>            <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"West Bengal"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Bengaluru"</span>          <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Karnataka"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Hyderabad"</span>          <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Telangana"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Lucknow"</span>            <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Uttar Pradesh"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Patna"</span>              <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Bihar"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Gurugram"</span>           <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Haryana"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Jaipur"</span>             <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Rajasthan"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Bhopal"</span>             <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Madhya Pradesh"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Amaravati"</span>          <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Andhra Pradesh"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Chandigarh"</span>         <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Chandigarh"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Coimbatore"</span>         <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Tamil Nadu"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Ernakulam"</span>          <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Kerala"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Guwahati"</span>           <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Assam"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Jorapokhar"</span>         <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Jharkhand"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Kochi"</span>              <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Kerala"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Shillong"</span>           <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Meghalaya"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Talcher"</span>            <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Odisha"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Thiruvananthapuram"</span> <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Kerala"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Visakhapatnam"</span>      <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Andhra Pradesh"</span><span class="p">,</span>
<span class="p">}</span>

<span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"City"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">map</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">city_to_state</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dropna</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">subset</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">])</span>

<span class="c1"># average AQI per state</span>
<span class="n">state_aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">)[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">mean</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reset_index</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">state_aqi</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">columns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Avg_AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">state_aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Avg_AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">state_aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Avg_AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">round</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># top 5 most and least polluted</span>
<span class="n">top5_dirty</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">state_aqi</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">nlargest</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span>  <span class="s2">"Avg_AQI"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">top5_clean</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">state_aqi</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">nsmallest</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Avg_AQI"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Most polluted states:"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">top5_dirty</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_string</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="se">\n</span><span class="s2">Least polluted states:"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">top5_clean</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_string</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">))</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
