<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=db084dba-328a-4cd5-89b3-a87af79bdbb6">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="Task-A-%E2%80%94-What-the-Chart-Shows">Task A — What the Chart Shows<a class="anchor-link" href="#Task-A-%E2%80%94-What-the-Chart-Shows">¶</a></h2><p>The pattern is more complicated than the hypothesis suggests.</p>
<p>Some of the most polluted states also show high crop production.
This is the key surprise. States like Delhi, Haryana and Uttar Pradesh
are both heavily polluted and heavy agricultural producers. The reason
is that the pollution and the farming come from the same source —
large scale crop cultivation followed by stubble burning drives both
the high output and the high AQI at the same time.</p>
<p>The least polluted states tend to be smaller states or states with
more forest and hill terrain where large scale farming is simply
not practiced. Their lower production reflects geography and land use,
not the benefit of cleaner air helping their crops grow.</p>
<p>This means the hypothesis cannot be confirmed or denied just by
comparing extremes. The relationship is hidden behind confounding
factors that this dataset cannot account for — rainfall levels,
irrigation access, soil type and farm size all explain production
differences far more directly than AQI does.</p>
<p>Correlation is not causation. A state being polluted and productive
at the same time does not mean pollution helps crops — it means
both come from the same farming activity.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=fc30ae6b-b261-4e87-a664-cfb4276df561">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="Task-B-%E2%80%94-Putting-a-Number-on-the-Relationship">Task B — Putting a Number on the Relationship<a class="anchor-link" href="#Task-B-%E2%80%94-Putting-a-Number-on-the-Relationship">¶</a></h2><p>The research team wants to know how strong the link is between
average state AQI and average crop production.</p>
<p>I will use a scatter plot with a regression line. This gives both:</p>
<ul>
<li>A visual picture of the relationship</li>
<li>The Pearson r value which measures strength and direction</li>
</ul>
<p>What r values mean in plain terms:</p>
<ul>
<li>r near 0 means no real linear relationship</li>
<li>r near +1 means both go up together</li>
<li>r near -1 means as one goes up the other goes down</li>
<li>r of 0.2 means AQI explains about 4% of production variation</li>
<li>r of 0.8 means AQI explains about 64% of production variation</li>
</ul>
<p>A weak r here does not mean pollution has no effect on crops.
It means the effect is hidden by stronger factors like farm size,
rainfall and irrigation which are not in this dataset.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=0cc86cd3-866b-4f01-83ab-9f6c85cdfd9f">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [103]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>
<span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">scipy</span> <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="n">stats</span>

<span class="c1"># load</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"city_day.csv"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">crop</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">read_csv</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"crop_production.csv"</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># prepare AQI state averages</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Date"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"Date"</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">errors</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"coerce"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dropna</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">subset</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">&gt;=</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">&lt;=</span> <span class="mi">1000</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="n">city_to_state</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="s2">"Ahmedabad"</span>          <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Gujarat"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Delhi"</span>              <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Delhi"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Mumbai"</span>             <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Maharashtra"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Chennai"</span>            <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Tamil Nadu"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Kolkata"</span>            <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"West Bengal"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Bengaluru"</span>          <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Karnataka"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Hyderabad"</span>          <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Telangana"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Lucknow"</span>            <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Uttar Pradesh"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Patna"</span>              <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Bihar"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Gurugram"</span>           <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Haryana"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Jaipur"</span>             <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Rajasthan"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Bhopal"</span>             <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Madhya Pradesh"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Amaravati"</span>          <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Andhra Pradesh"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Chandigarh"</span>         <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Chandigarh"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Coimbatore"</span>         <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Tamil Nadu"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Ernakulam"</span>          <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Kerala"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Guwahati"</span>           <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Assam"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Jorapokhar"</span>         <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Jharkhand"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Kochi"</span>              <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Kerala"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Shillong"</span>           <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Meghalaya"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Talcher"</span>            <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Odisha"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Thiruvananthapuram"</span> <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Kerala"</span><span class="p">,</span>
    <span class="s2">"Visakhapatnam"</span>      <span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"Andhra Pradesh"</span><span class="p">,</span>
<span class="p">}</span>

<span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"City"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">map</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">city_to_state</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dropna</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">subset</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">state_aqi</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">aqi</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">)[</span><span class="s2">"AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">mean</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reset_index</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">state_aqi</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">columns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Avg_AQI"</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="c1"># prepare crop state totals</span>
<span class="n">crop</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">crop</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">rename</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">columns</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">{</span><span class="s2">"State_Name"</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">})</span>
<span class="n">state_crop</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">crop</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">groupby</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">)[</span><span class="s2">"Production"</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">sum</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reset_index</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">state_crop</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">columns</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Total_Production"</span><span class="p">]</span>

<span class="c1"># merge</span>
<span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">merge</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">state_aqi</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">state_crop</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">on</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"State"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">how</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"inner"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">data</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">dropna</span><span class="p">()</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"States in merged data:"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">data</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">to_string</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">False</span><span class="p">))</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
